cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this code, the phrase datasets, or the published measurements,
  please cite this repository and the companion site.
title: "patientwords-engine: circuit-level analysis of clinical vs. patient language in language models"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Green
    given-names: Michael D.
repository-code: "https://github.com/michaeldgreenphd/patientwords-engine"
url: "https://michaeldgreenphd.github.io/patientwords/"
date-released: 2026-07-08
keywords:
  - mechanistic interpretability
  - attribution graphs
  - health communication
  - patient language
  - language models
  - gemma-2-2b
abstract: >-
  Pipeline for measuring how language models shift next-token predictions when
  standard clinical terminology is replaced by the colloquial language patients
  use: LLM-generated stress pairs with programmatic validation, hosted
  attribution-graph tracing (circuit-tracer via Neuronpedia, Gemma Scope
  transcoders), cross-model next-token measurement, a care-urgency shift
  instrument, and a translation-mitigation experiment. Research code, work in
  progress; findings are preliminary. The study measures model probabilities
  only and is not a medical tool.
